<div class="yui-content">
<div id="wiki-tab-0-0">
<p>Walking down the halls of Site-104, you flip through the report that was tossed on your desk this morning. The Internal Investigations Department sent you to look into a suicide. The suicide of a Doctor Dan H. F████████.</p>
<p>Sometimes your job is figuring out what went wrong in the moments before a containment breach destroyed a facility. Other times it's looking into why a fresh out of grad school researcher was found dead in his office. The autopsy says it was an overdose of injected paralytics.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><sup>Start The Investigation - <strong>Click Tab 05</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>There are worse ways to start a Thursday.</em></sup></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-1" style="display:none">
<p>&quot;Mike was it? I'd like to see the security footage for the containment here. Maybe there's something up with Dr. F that will help with this.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;That's err, that's going to be tricky&#8230; You see, the tapes from yesterday, they were corrupted. Must have been anomalous or something.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;You think it's an anomalous effect of the chicken?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Yeah that's probably what happened! It's been really freaking me out. I'm lucky the files were corrupted before I saw them, you know? Otherwise, I might have been exposed to the same anomaly that got Dan and you'd be investigating two suicides maybe!&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p><sup>Wrap Up Your Investigation - <strong>Click Tab 34</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>Seems there's nothing much more to investigate here.</em></sup></p>
<p><sup>Ask About The Corrupted Footage - <strong>Click Tab 08</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>Corrupted data could still mean something, right?</em></sup><br />
<sup><em>flavor</em></sup></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-2" style="display:none">
<p>The containment area is pretty standard for the bioresearch site. At the center of the room is an animal containment cage with a few chickens inside. (Someone must have been concerned chicken 404 would get lonely) At the far end of the cage is the white plane that can only be SCP-3620 moving around the other chickens.</p>
<p>A D-Class personnel is between you and the cage with their back to you, taking notes on a clipboard. No one else is in the room. Though a security camera in the corner reminds you you're never truly alone in the Foundation.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><sup>Talk To The D-Class Personnel - <strong>Click Tab 13</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>They may not be full on researchers, but they work hands-on with a lot of SCPs.</em></sup></p>
<p><sup>Take A Closer Look At SCP-3620 - <strong>Click Tab 17</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>The shape of it is strange. A white flat plane that moves like a chicken&#8230;</em></sup></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-3" style="display:none">
<p>&quot;Those papers, let me take a look at them.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Oh? Of course.&quot;</p>
<p>You look over the documents Dr. F████████ was working on for SCP-3620. Your eyes bother you when you read too long, but nothing seems out of place. They were trying to increase the feed density which could, in turn, allow them to chop off more chicken without worrying too much about where it was all coming from.</p>
<p>Seems like a nice way to ignore the fact that it's a nonexistent, infinite chicken they're pulling this all out of. It's no wonder containment breaches happen so often around here, no one can just leave things the way they found it! There are some notes on Dr. F████████'s computer about a discrepancy with the record input and output weights but Dr. Charlene M████ says she hadn't been informed of this.</p>
<p>The last update was just 14 hours ago. The last time anyone saw F████████ before he was found at his desk here, stiff as a board. In this very seat. Might be a good time to call it quits here. Nothing else in his computer is of note.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><sup>Investigate Dr. Charlene M████ More - <strong>Click Tab 36</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>Dr. Charlene M████ doesn't seem bothered by the death of one of her junior researchers, does she?</em></sup></p>
<p><sup>Head Back To The Containment Area - <strong>Click Tab 21</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>This place has already been looked over by forensic.</em></sup></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-4" style="display:none">
<p>Before you can finish the report you arrive at the anomalous animal containment wing housing SCP-3620, which Dr. F████████ was assigned to. For this case you've been granted access to the SCP file and its related documents. (But for some reason, your clearance doesn't let you see Dr. F's unblocked out last name. Got to love bureaucracy) It's already 11 am and you want to get a move on this before things go cold.</p>
<p>SCP-3620, &quot;Data Expunged the Chicken,&quot; Object Class: Safe. Still, the report brings into question if the suicide was caused by an anomalous effect or not. All this time in containment and they still don't know everything this SCP is capable of.</p>
<p>What do you want to do?</p>
<blockquote>
<p><sup>Read The SCP File First - <strong>Click Tab 10</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>Better to know what you're getting into.</em></sup></p>
<p><sup>Enter The Containment Area - <strong>Click Tab 19</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>Your job is to investigate a suicide, not the SCP.</em></sup></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-5" style="display:none">
<p>&quot;Danny? What can I tell you about the guy? I didn't know him all that well. We started at the same time on SCP-3620. He was a real serious kind of guy. Real stick in the mud, you know?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Did he seem distressed or distracted last time you saw him?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Yeah, you know what, he really did seem off. He closed the containment last night, I watched him do it like it always does, locking it behind him. Watched him walk off. Didn't realize I'd be the last person to see him alive. It's strange to think about.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;But how did he seem?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Oh, he seemed really out of it. Real sad, or just like, like almost in a trance? If it was something that SCP-3620 did, maybe it put the whammy on him just before that? Guess I'm lucky it didn't get me too since I would have just been out here watching the door before lockdown for the night.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Is there anything else you can tell me?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Cross-contamination man, you never know what's going to get you. Everyone's so worried about the statues that will snap your neck, but no one knows when some critter is going to fry your liver because some other thing you're exposed to is messing with your mind, you know?&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p><sup>Go Talk To The D-Class Personnel - <strong>Click Tab 15</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>You think you recall her name was Clara.</em></sup></p>
<p><sup>Go Talk To Dr. Charlene M████ - <strong>Click Tab 12</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>A researcher should know more about this than these two.</em></sup></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-6" style="display:none">
<p>&quot;Cross-contamination? That's just like getting &quot;keter duty&quot; as punishment or monthly terminations for us D-class! Maybe, somewhere something like that happened, but then it became a rumor and spread like wild! These days cross-testing is pretty common and there's usually very little risk involved.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Do others on your assignment feel the same?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Well, there aren't too many that I've talked to. Dr. Charlene M████ is so methodical, she doesn't seem to be worried about death like the rest of us might. Seems a little out of touch if you ask me. On the other end, the main Security Personnel, Mike, he's an ass that cares a bit too much about his own skin. He usually gets bored and tries to chat me up during the day. I just kind of respond with a grunt cause I don't much like him.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;What does he talk to you about? Well, at you about?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;What SCPs would be cool to take home. If SCP-whatever fought SCP-whatever, who would win. Last week he was asking me if any of our research revealed how best to up Spongy's meat. If it would be possible to get some tomatoes from SCP-504 to make an anomalous sandwich! Speak of the devil..&quot;</p>
<p>You follow Clara's eyes to see a security personnel standing in the doorway.</p>
<p>&quot;Anyways, I'll get back to work unless you have anything else you need. Dr. Charlene M████ can give you access to Dr. F████████'s files if you need them.&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p><sup>Go Talk To Security Personnel Mike - <strong>Click Tab 11</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>Let's see what he knows about all this.</em></sup></p>
<p><sup>Go Talk To Dr. Charlene M████ - <strong>Click Tab 22</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>There might be something more in the office.</em></sup></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-7" style="display:none">
<p>&quot;The corrupted files could still help us get to the bottom of this.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Ah, uh, yeah. They would, but I can't give them to you.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;As a member of the internal review committee, I have the authorization to access all related research and containment data related to SCP-3620. You need to give me those files.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Well, that's the tricky thing. I uh, I had to delete them.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;So you're telling me the security footage for the containment area got corrupted and you went ahead and deleted it?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Yes sir.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Even though that breaks protocol?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;I- Ah, I was afraid that whatever had affected Dan was on the footage, even though it was corrupted. Didn't- didn't want to risk it getting out and getting other killed, ya know? I don't want a broke chicken getting in my head and making me off myself!&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p><sup>Mike Probably Had The Right Idea - <strong>Click Tab 34</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>He might have broke protocol, but he also might have saved lives.</em></sup></p>
<p><sup>Protocol Is Protocol - <strong>Click Tab 32</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>Mike has to be held responsible for his lapse in protocol.</em></sup></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-8" style="display:none">
<p>Accessing the security footage doesn't seem to be an issue and last night's entry looks just as expected. Dr. F leaves the containment area after locking up, everyone else had already headed out for the night, he goes to his office, next day he's found dead at his desk.</p>
<p>But something Clara said urges you to keep looking. You go over the last few days, watching for anything of note, anything off. Your eyes start to blur over as you skim through hours and hours of footage, but you stay attentive. Finally, your work pays off! You almost didn't even catch it!</p>
<p>The footage from last night had been copied from another night a few weeks back! Someone tried to cover it up, but there's no mistaking it. You make a few calls and the data scrubbers work their magic!</p>
<blockquote>
<p><sup>Finish This Investigation - <strong>Click Tab 14</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>Something smells here and the lost security footage should reveal it.</em></sup></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-9" style="display:none">
<p>Standing outside the containment area, you read through the whole file. Thankfully it's not a massive document with a dozen addendums and bizarre requirements in order to approach the thing. Still, a few researchers pass by you before you finish the file.</p>
<div class="scp-image-block block-right" style="width:300px;"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/the-suicide-of-dr-f/scp-3620.jpg" style="width:300px;" alt="scp-3620.jpg" class="image" />
<div class="scp-image-caption" style="width:300px;">
<p>SCP-3620 as photographed on initial discovery</p>
</div>
</div>
<p>Item #: SCP-3620 &quot;Data Expunged the Chicken,&quot; Object Class: Safe <em>(Pending current investigation)</em>, the thing is basically a chicken that's not there. Instead, it's, <em>&quot;a two-dimensional white plane featuring a pictograph and a series of curved lines hypothetized to be language.&quot;</em></p>
<p>You stop a moment and try to picture this in your mind.</p>
<p><em>&quot;confirmed by genetic testing<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-1')">1</a></sup> to be an approximately 5-year-old female domestic chicken (Gallus gallus domesticus). Behavior and vocalizations are consistent with those of a chicken, as are the appearance of all tissue samples taken.&quot;</em></p>
<p>So it's a chicken that failed to load. It clucks like a chicken, it weighs as much as a chicken, it lays eggs like a chicken. But unlike a chicken, it hasn't aged in the 35 years it's been here, it's physically invariant. You can cut all the legs and wings and breast meat you like and it'll still be clucking away with more to spare, and it looks like broken image link on Wikipedia. Got it.</p>
<p>What do you want to do?</p>
<blockquote>
<p><sup>Head Into The Containment Area - <strong>Click Tab 03</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>Time to meet this expunged chicken.</em></sup></p>
<p><sup>Head To Dr. F's Office - <strong>Click Tab 12</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>This SCP isn't sentient, the other researchers might know something.</em></sup></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-10" style="display:none">
<p>&quot;Agent R███████, internal review committee, nice to meet you. Mike is it?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Hey, the one and only. Well, there's another Mike on site but he's on another wing rotation. You're here about Dan then?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Yes, anything you can tell me about last night or this week?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Just that it's got me scared shitless! Dan the man, he was a very serious guy, kind of an ass, but eh, I won't speak ill of the deceased. Uh, just you know, this is what we always worry about on these &quot;safe&quot; SCPs. That they'll mess with you, mix with another SCP you've been exposed to.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Did the other personnel on SCP-3620 feel the same?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Oh sure, yeah, we all talked about it, some maybe more than others. Me and Danny, we chatted about it a few times. Researchers, you know, they see a lot more than we do usually, though Dan was pretty new to all this. The D-Class, the ones that know about other SCPs, they're pretty freaked out about it too. They think it's a new property like it's growing maybe, you know?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;So you've always been concerned with cross-testing and cross SCP contamination?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Definitely, definitely. One of my biggest fears working here. Always makes me uneasy when the researchers talk about it. Dr. Charlene M████ going on about Spongy being an endless food supply like there's no issue with it looking like some sort of weird computer glitch! If I had it my way, we'd just destroy the ones we could and lock the others up and throw away the keys. Be done with it.&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p><sup>Talk With Dr. Charlene M████ To Shed Some Light - <strong>Click Tab 22</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>Mike seems a little worked up, maybe someone more level headed is better to talk to.</em></sup></p>
<p><sup>Dr. Charlene M████ Is Suspect Number 1 - <strong>Click Tab 36</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>The Doctor is hiding something and you're going to get to the bottom of it!</em></sup></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-11" style="display:none">
<p>Arriving at Dr. F████████'s office you meet Dr. Charlene M████, who doesn't seem overly bothered that a colleague just killed himself in this room last night.</p>
<p>&quot;Dr. Charlene M████, can you tell us about Mr. F████████?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Well, I can tell you he'd get pissed off at you calling him &quot;mister&quot; F████████.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Ah, my apologies. Pretty proud of his degree then?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;I'd say so. Thought he was pretty bright, well, before SCP-3620 and all this. He was pretty new to the team — fresh out of grad school — this was his first assignment here. We were working on seeing if Spongy could, sorry SCP-3620-&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Spongy is fine. Nicknames are non-standard but it is kind of catchy.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Thanks. If Spongy, could be used as a renewable food source. She's genetically a normal chicken, and so when you pull off a wing or a leg or whatever, it's the same as any old chicken meat. Besides the visual anomaly, her physical properties cause a new part to pop right back into existence no matter how much we chop off. We do have to try to keep things balanced. &quot;Wanted Buffalo wings so badly we threw off Earth's orbit&quot; would be one of the most embarrassing XKs to cause, you know?&quot;</p>
<p>Dr. Charlene M████ goes on to tell you about the research he and Dan were doing, attempting to increase the feed density so they could collect more from Spongy per day. Keep anything around long enough in the Foundation and eventually, someone will try to put it to use. Infinite pizza and chicken wings sound like a gimmicky bar you would frequent back in college.</p>
<p>You press her about the anomalous properties of SCP-3620, if she thought this could have been caused by some unknown memetic effect or something.</p>
<p>&quot;I do not. At least, not like a memetic or telepathic effect. I've personally been studying this for 5 years now, it's been in custody since the 80s, and this is the first time anything like this has happened. You tend to become a bit numb to the weirdness around here, but someone as new as Daniel… We think the &quot;Euclids&quot; and the &quot;Keters&quot; as the scary ones, so we forget that even &quot;Safe&quot; skips can destroy someone's whole worldview, you know?&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p><sup>Head Back To The Containment Area - <strong>Click Tab 21</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>There's nothing more to investigate in the office.</em></sup></p>
<p><sup>Look At The Security Footage- <strong>Click Tab 29</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>There's got to be something caught on video.</em></sup></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-12" style="display:none">
<p>&quot;Hey, Agent R███████, internal review committee. Can I talk to you a moment?&quot;</p>
<p>The D-Class personnel turns to you. She's wearing the standard orange jumpsuit, holding a clipboard and pen. She tucks the clipboard under her arm and approaches you.</p>
<p>&quot;Sure thing, just finished counting the eggs this morning. You here about the guy who killed himself?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Yeah, what do you know about it? The report was just given to me this morning. Says it might be related to the anomalous properties of SCP-3620? But the file says-&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Doesn't say anything about magical mind rays that make you want to kill yourself. Yeah, I don't think it's anything to do with that.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;You feel pretty certain of that?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Yeah, I'd bet my life on it. I've been working this assignment for a few years now. Grew up on a farm, think that's why I got this and not some other SCP to test. I've eaten every part of this chicken. Slept in this room for a week. Yell at it, told it my darkest secrets, stared at it so long I could see the image when I closed my eyes. Everything you can imagine. But nothing ever happened. The shit is weird but it's mainly just weird to look at. Usually gives new folks a headache.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;It is a bit of a trip&#8230;&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Dr. Charlene M████ is the lead researcher though. She'll back up that nothing strange comes from this chicken besides endless chicken wings.&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p><sup>Go To Dr. F's Office - <strong>Click Tab 28</strong></sup><br />
