</blockquote>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-29" style="display:none">
<p>You find Dr. Charlene M████ back at the containment area, talking with the D-Class personnel from earlier. Neither seems overly happy to see you and Clara goes back to managing the chickens when you approach. Dr. Charlene M████ greets you, though indifferently.</p>
<p>&quot;Are you Dr. Charlene M████? Can you tell us about Mr. F████████?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Well, I can tell you he'd get pissed off at you calling him &quot;mister&quot; instead of &quot;doctor&quot;.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;My apologies, Dr. F████████.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;He was pretty new to the team, this was his first assignment at the site. We were working to see if we could increase the amount of feed she was intaking in a day. You see, she's basically a normal chicken, all things considered. You can pull some meat off her and it acts the same as any other chicken breast, but you can keep going back for more and she stays the same.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;And you don't think this has had anomalous side effects? Maybe from eating too much of it or cutting more and more off of it?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Are you asking in regards to what happened to Dan?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Could something like the feeding protocol have triggered an effect?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;It's unlikely. We're bringing in a few more D-class to try and recreate it, but nothing has caused a problem before now.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;So in your opinion, do you feel Dr. F████████'s suicide was an anomalous effect created by SCP-3620?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;I do not. My theory is it's not like a memetic or telepathic effect. I've been studying this for three years now, and it's been in containment for thirty-five. This is the first time anything like this has happened. You tend to become a bit numb to the weirdness around here, but someone as new as Dan… We think of the Euclids and the Keters as the scary ones, so we forget that even quote-unquote-safe skips can destroy someone's whole worldview, you know?&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p><sup>File Your Report - <strong>Click Tab 34</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>Your investigation is complete here.</em></sup></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-30" style="display:none">
<p>&quot;Yeah, I just- just stared at the damn chicken error message too long.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Ah, that'll do it. Messed my head up pretty good the first time I saw it too. I'm real glad you guys are investigating this though. Really don't want to end up like Danny boy. Now that I take a look at ya, you don't look too good. Do you want to go lay down?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;I'm fine, it's just a headache, just probably need a little-&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Hey, no need to play the tough guy. This could be like what happened to Dan! I'll get ya to the infirmary and they'll make sure this isn't something anomalous or anything. Don't worry buddy, I got ya.&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p><sup>Mike Helps You To The Infirmary - <strong>Click Tab 35</strong></sup><br />
<sup><em>You'll go get this checked out.</em></sup></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-31" style="display:none">
<p>Mike the Security Personnel is detained and further investigations are carried out into his activities while assigned to SCP-3620.</p>
<p>It is uncovered that he had been accessing SCP-3620 after normal hours, collecting unauthorized chicken meat, and smuggling it off-site. Data recovery on the deleted security footage revealed no corruption and that Mike was attempting to destroy evidence of his involvement in junior researcher Dr. Daniel F████████'s death.</p>
<p>The footage showed Mike accessing SCP-3620 after hours when Dr. Daniel enters the containment area and confronts him. Security Personnel Mike was interrupted before he could administer the injected paralytic to SCP-3620 and during the following struggle injected it into Dr. F████████ instead. The footage then shows Security Personnel Mike dragging the body of Dr. F████████ out of the containment area and towards the office. A document found on Dr. F████████'s office computer noted a discrepancy in SCP-3620's weight and output, with the last update minutes before the confrontation on the recovered footage.</p>
<p>The evidence continues and Security Personnel Mike is brought to justice by a jury of his peers. Dr. Charlene M████ stayed on as the lead researcher while Clara continued her overseeing daily containment procedures of SCP-3620. Testing on utilizing SCP-3620 as a source of renewable food continued.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><sup>Ending 3 - <strong>The End</strong></sup></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-32" style="display:none">
<p>No one told you to click this tab now did they? You're just looking around at all the answers, all the different possibilities to pick from! Well, you've found this one lonely tab. It leads nowhere, and nowhere leads to it. Unless you think outside the box, though thinking like that doesn't really get rewarded normally. Definitely not here, not now.</p>
<p>Really, this murder mystery would make even less sense if you tried to read it by going straight on to every tab. Even less so if you're skipping around! Here's hoping you didn't misclick, or that you didn't forget where you were. Or the chance that there's a forgotten direction that got you here. That would be on me though, my bad.</p>
<p>Anyways, hope you had fun! I hate this gimmick now! Way too tricky keeping everything straight as things begin to branch out!</p>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-33" style="display:none">
<p>The death of Dr. Daniel H. F████████ was ruled a suicide. The committee voted to keep the object classification as &quot;Safe&quot; for SCP-3620. No new anomalous effects were recorded despite further D-Class and researcher testing. Backup systems were implemented to prevent future security footage corruption, though no future incidents were reported.</p>
<p>Dr. Charlene M████ stayed on as lead researcher. The D-Class named Clara continued her assignment overseeing daily care and containment of SCP-3620. Security Personnel Mike requested a transfer to another SCP citing, &quot;unease around Spongy&quot; since the suicide. His request was granted.</p>
<p>You filed your report and moved on with your life. Well, at least until the next file was tossed on your desk to investigate. Exactly how did a D-Class personnel walk out of a secure facility with a 'Get Out Of Jail Free' card from a Monopólio set?</p>
<blockquote>
<p><sup>Ending 1 - <strong>The End</strong></sup></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-34" style="display:none">
<p>At the infirmary, you get to rest up, under observation of course, and by the end of the day, you're feeling better. No suicidal thoughts or other symptoms to report! Seems you just got hit by a more severe headache than others.</p>
<p>Further testing provided no evidence that SCP-3620 had a direct role in Dr. F████████'s suicide. The committee would vote to keep the classification as &quot;Safe&quot; for now.</p>
<p>Dr. Charlene M████ continued work as the lead researcher. Clara the D-Class stayed on the assignment overseeing daily care and containment of SCP-3620 as did Security Personnel Mike. Your report, though uneventful, was filed on this incident. Life went on. Well, at least for a few months before another death was reported around SCP-3620 and your report was called into question.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><sup>Ending 2 - <strong>The End</strong></sup></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-35" style="display:none">
<p>Further investigation into Dr. Charlene M████ reveals nothing out of the ordinary. Their research was looking promising but has been halted until further testing proves Dr. F████████'s suicide was unrelated to the effects of <a href="/scp-3620">SCP-3620</a>. Dr. Charlene M████ continued work as the lead researcher, the D-Class stayed on the assignment overseeing daily care as did the Security Personnel.</p>
<p>Dr. Charlene M████'s final statement on the case sticks with you well after you've moved onto other investigations:</p>
<p>&quot;You tend to become a bit numb to the weirdness around here, but someone as new as Dan… We think of the Euclids and the Keters as the scary ones, so we forget that even quote-unquote-safe skips can destroy someone's whole worldview, you know?&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p><sup>Ending 4 - <strong>The End</strong></sup></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
